# Known bare `db.select()` joins that exceed D1's 100-column result-row cap.
# Each entry is `repo-relative/path.ts:<line>` and suppresses the ERROR exit
# code from scripts/check-d1-100col-joins.ts for that specific call site.
#
# These are real bugs (D1 silently returns zero rows when triggered) but
# they're hidden today because the queries' WHERE clauses or data state
# don't currently trigger result-rows that would exceed the cap. Each
# needs a follow-up PR that narrows the projection.
#
# Add NEW entries here only with a tracking-issue link and explicit reason.
# The CI script keeps these visible in every run so the queue stays in
# front of the team.
#
# Empty as of the PR that cleared the last entries (see #361). All real
# violations have been narrowed; the former false-positive entries
# (db.batch arrays) were resolved by the chain-detection improvement in
# scripts/check-d1-100col-joins.ts (collectJoinChainTables stops at the
# first non-from/join chain method, so independent selects inside a
# db.batch([...]) array are evaluated correctly).
